  • I wrote my name in README.md and also added TsuPeiChiu as a collaborator to my repo.

(2) High-throughput binding assays: Briefly describe¶

(a) the in vitro experiments SELEX-seq and PBM, and¶

(b) the in vivo experiment ChlP-seq.¶

(c) Compare and discuss the advantage and disadvantage of these methods. 10 pts.¶

(3) Preparation of high-throughput in vitro data analysis:¶

(a) Download and install R (version >= 3.3.0) from https://www.r-project.org.¶

(b) Install Bioconductor on your R platform. The installation instruction can be found at https://www.bioconductor.org/install/.¶

(c) Install package DNAshaper on your R platform. The installation instruction can be found at https://www.bioconductor.org/packages/devel/bioc/html/DNAshaper.html¶

(d) Install the machine learning package caret on your R platform. The installation instruction can be found at https://github.com/topepo/caret¶

%%R
## helper function for feature vector
get_feature_vector = function(fn, featureType=c("1-mer", "1-shape")){
  pred <- getShape(fn)
  featureVector <- encodeSeqShape(fn, pred, featureType)
  return(featureVector)
}

## 1mer+shape
mad_fv_1mer_shape <- get_feature_vector(mad_seq,featureType=c("1-mer", "1-shape"))
max_fv_1mer_shape <- get_feature_vector(max_seq,featureType=c("1-mer", "1-shape"))
myc_fv_1mer_shape <- get_feature_vector(myc_seq,featureType=c("1-mer", "1-shape"))

## 1mer only
mad_fv_1mer <- get_feature_vector(mad_seq, featureType=c("1-mer"))
max_fv_1mer <- get_feature_vector(max_seq, featureType=c("1-mer"))
myc_fv_1mer <- get_feature_vector(myc_seq, featureType=c("1-mer"))

%%R
## helper function for build MLR model
build_MLR_model <- function(affinity_table, fv, fold){
  exp_data <- read.table(affinity_table)
  df <- data.frame(affinity=exp_data$V2, fv)
  train_ctrl <- trainControl(method ="cv", number=fold, savePredictions = TRUE)
  model <- train(affinity~ ., data=df, trControl=train_ctrl,
                 method="lm", preProcess=NULL)
  return(model)
}

## Binding Affinity files 
mad_ba = paste0(path,"/gcPBM/Mad.txt")
max_ba = paste0(path,"/gcPBM/Max.txt")
myc_ba = paste0(path,"/gcPBM/Myc.txt")

## 1mer+shape
mad_model_1mer_shape <- build_MLR_model(mad_ba, mad_fv_1mer_shape, 10)
max_model_1mer_shape <- build_MLR_model(max_ba, max_fv_1mer_shape, 10)
myc_model_1mer_shape <- build_MLR_model(myc_ba, myc_fv_1mer_shape, 10)

## 1mer only
mad_model_1mer <- build_MLR_model(mad_ba, mad_fv_1mer, 10)
max_model_1mer <- build_MLR_model(max_ba, max_fv_1mer, 10)
myc_model_1mer <- build_MLR_model(myc_ba, myc_fv_1mer, 10)

%%R
## helper function for getting rsquared value
get_rsquared <- function(model){
  return(model$results$Rsquared)
}

## getting rsquared
print(c(get_rsquared(mad_model_1mer_shape),get_rsquared(max_model_1mer_shape),get_rsquared(myc_model_1mer_shape)))
print(c(get_rsquared(mad_model_1mer),get_rsquared(max_model_1mer),get_rsquared(myc_model_1mer)))

In [11]:
%%R -w 540 -h 480 -u px
## making dataframe for plotting
comp_model <- data.frame(
  TFs = c("Mad","Max","Myc"),
  rsqr_1mer = c(get_rsquared(mad_model_1mer),get_rsquared(max_model_1mer),get_rsquared(myc_model_1mer)),
  rsqr_1mer_shape = c(get_rsquared(mad_model_1mer_shape),get_rsquared(max_model_1mer_shape),get_rsquared(myc_model_1mer_shape))
)

## plotting
ggscatter(comp_model, x="rsqr_1mer", y="rsqr_1mer_shape", ylim=c(0,1.0), xlim=c(0,1.0), color="TFs", shape="TFs", theme=theme_pubclean(), legend="right") + geom_abline(intercept=0, slope=1, linetype="dashed") + xlab(expression(atop("1mer "*R^{2}, "(sequence+shape model)"))) + ylab(expression(atop("1mer+shape "*R^{2},"(sequence model)")))

%%R 

## helper function for emsembl plotting
get_ensembl_plots <- function(fn){
    pred <- getShape(fn)
    par(mfrow=c(2,4))
    plotShape(pred$MGW)
    plotShape(pred$ProT)
    plotShape(pred$Roll)
    plotShape(pred$HelT)
    heatShape(pred$MGW,dim(pred$MGW)[2])
    heatShape(pred$ProT,dim(pred$ProT)[2])
    heatShape(pred$Roll,dim(pred$Roll)[2])
    heatShape(pred$HelT,dim(pred$HelT)[2]) 
}

%%R
## Generate data for the classifcation (assign Y to bound and N to non-bound)
# bound_500
bound_500_fasta <- readDNAStringSet(bound_500_seq)
bound_txt <- data.frame(seq=paste(bound_500_fasta), isBound="Y")

# unbound_500
unbound_500_fasta <- readDNAStringSet(unbound_500_seq)
unbound_txt <- data.frame(seq=paste(unbound_500_fasta), isBound="N")

# merge two datasets
writeXStringSet( c(bound_500_fasta, unbound_500_fasta), paste0(path, "/CTCF/ctcf.fa"))
exp_data <- rbind(bound_txt, unbound_txt)

## Logistic regression

                             savePredictions = TRUE, classProbs = TRUE)

               method = "glm", family = binomial, metric ="ROC")

## Plot AUROC
prediction <- prediction( model$pred$Y, model$pred$obs )
performance <- performance( prediction, "tpr", "fpr" )
plot(performance)

## Caluculate AUROC
auc <- performance(prediction, "auc")
auc <- unlist(slot(auc, "y.values"))
print(paste("auc:",auc))

Same procedures with pre-computed models with bound/unbound_30, bound/unbound¶
In [6]:
%%R
## helper function for plotting and calculating AUROC
plot_cal_AUROC <- function(model){
    ## Plot AUROC
    prediction <- prediction( model$pred$Y, model$pred$obs )
    performance <- performance( prediction, "tpr", "fpr" )
    plot(performance)
    
    ## Caluculate AUROC
    auc <- performance(prediction, "auc")
    auc <- unlist(slot(auc, "y.values"))
    print(paste("auc:",auc))
    
}
In [7]:
%%R -w 640 -h 480 -u px
##Pre-computed model with bound_30, unbound_30
model_30 <- readRDS("model_30.rds")
plot_cal_AUROC(model_30)
